017 singles]]\n[[Category:2017 songs]]\n[[Category:Billboard Adult Top 40 number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Billboard Alternative Songs number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Imagine Dragons songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Joel Little]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Daniel Platzman]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Ben McKee]]\n[[Category:Interscope Records singles]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Wayne Sermon]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Dan Reynolds (musician)]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Russia]]\n[[Category:Utah Jazz]]\n[[Category:Vegas Golden Knights]]\n", "name_user": "156.204.147.168", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Whatever_It_Takes_(Imagine_Dragons_song)"}
{"title_page": "Ponnambalam (actor)", "text_new": "{{Cleanup bare URLs|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Ponnambalam\n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1963|11|11}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nettv4u.com/celebrity/tamil/movie-actor/ponnambalam |title=Tamil Movie Actor Ponnambalam - Nettv4u |publisher= |accessdate=1 October 2016}}</ref>\n| birth_place        = \n| residence          = [[Chennai]], [[Tamil Nadu]], India\n| occupation         = Film actor, stunt performer, film director\n| yearsactive        = 1987\u2013present\n| height             = \n| spouse             = \n| children           = \n}}\n\n'''Ponnambalam''' (born 11 November 1963) is an Indian [[film actor]] who has predominantly appeared in [[Tamil cinema|Tamil]] language films. He is best known for playing antagonistic roles in Indian films during the 1990s, notably appearing in films such as ''[[Nattamai]]'' (1994), ''[[Muthu (1995 film)|Muthu]]'' (1995) and ''[[Amarkalam]]'' (1999).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cinesouth.com/cgi-bin/persondb.cgi?name=ponnambalam |title=\u0b9f\u0bcb\u0b9f\u0bcb\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0bb0\u0b83\u0baa\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bcb\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1 \u2014 Tamil Kavithai -- \u0ba4\u0bae\u0bbf\u0bb4\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd - \u0ba8\u0bc2\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc1 \u0b95\u0ba3\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd! |publisher= |accessdate=1 October 2016}}</ref> Later in his career, Ponnambalam also appeared in a few leading roles, while also taking up the mantle of director and producer.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/interview/6126.html |title=Tamil Celebrity Interview - IndiaGlitz.com |publisher= |accessdate=1 October 2016}}</ref> \n\n==Career==\nPonnambalam made his debut in cinema as a stuntman, and often appeared as an extra fighter in films, starring in minor roles in films including ''[[Apoorva Sagodharargal (1989 film)|Apoorva Sagodharargal]]'' (1989) and ''[[Michael Madana Kama Rajan]]'' (1990). As a result of his proficiency as a stuntman, he later received the nickname \"Spare Parts\" Ponnambalam as no part of his body was ever injured or fractured.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/cinema-veeran-aishwarya-dhanush-pays-a-glorious-tribute-to-the-stuntmen-of-tamil-cinema-3743325.html |title=Cinema Veeran : Aishwarya Dhanush pays a glorious tribute to the stuntmen Of Tamil cinema |date=2017-06-25 |work=Firstpost |access-date=2017-07-19 |language=en-US}}</ref> He made a breakthrough as an actor following the success of [[P. Vasu]]'s ''[[Walter Vetrivel]]'' (1993), and subsequently starred in several prominent Tamil films in the 1990s in villainous roles. Notable characters her portrayed including his work in ''[[Nattamai]]'' (1994), ''[[Muthu (1995 film)|Muthu]]'' (1995) and ''[[Amarkalam]]'' (1999). Ponnambalam also played the lead roles in film including the action drama ''Muthal Echarikkai'' (1999) and ''Ammaiyappa'' (2002), where he featured alongside actress Roshini. Reviewing the film, a critic noted \"the movie does little other than prove conclusively that Ponnambalam is not cut out to be a hero\", and that \"though he picks a role that suits his build, emotes surprisingly well and fights aggressively, his looks make it difficult for us to accept him as a conventional leading man\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://jfwonline.com/article/bigg-boss-tamil-all-you-need-to-know-about-this-seasons-contestants/|title=Bigg Boss Tamil: All You Need To Know About This Season\u2019s Contestants!}}</ref>\n\nPonnambalam turned director and producer through the film, ''[[Pattaya Kelappu]]'', starring [[Sriman (actor)|Sriman]] in the lead role. Despite beginning in 2004, the film had a delayed release, while another directorial venture titled ''Thethi 32'' was subsequently dropped.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tKbxcnWqYYM</ref> Ponnambalam began a project titled ''Idiyudan Koodiya Mazhai'' during 2010, starring newcomers in the lead roles. Despite beginning production, the film was shelved and eventually did not have a theatrical release.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/may-10-04/ponnambalam-31-05-10.html|title=Ponnambalam - Tamil Movie News - Villain with a film - Ponnambalam &#124; Idiyudan Koodiya Mazhai &#124; Chandranath - Behindwoods.com|website=www.behindwoods.com}}</ref> His acting commitments thereafter also decreased, with notable appearances in the period including roles as a village chief in ''[[Thamizh Padam]]'' (2010) and characters in ''[[Venghai]]'' (2011) and the historical drama, ''[[Ponnar Shankar (film)|Ponnar Shankar]]'' (2011).\n\nIn 2018, Ponnambalam took part in the second season of the reality show ''[[Bigg Boss Tamil 2|Bigg Boss Tamil]]'' hosted by [[Kamal Haasan]]. His stay in the house was controversial, as he was accused of making [[misogyny|misogynistic]] comments against the female housemates, particularly against [[Yashika Aanand]], [[Aishwarya Dutta]], Mamathi Chari and [[Mumtaj]] and was nominated each week for the eviction from the second week of the show onwards.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sify.com/movies/bigg-boss-2-honour-culture-and-slander-news-tamil-shkqtihfbccci.html|title=Bigg Boss 2: Honour, Culture and Slander|website=Sify}}</ref> He was evicted during the eighth week of the show during mid-August 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/bigg-boss-tamil-eviction-live-sendrayan-escapes-ponnambalam-janani-exit-kamals-show-says-ibt-777619|title=Bigg Boss Tamil elimination: Ponnambalam evicted; his ouster gets mixed response from netizens|first=Prakash|last=Upadhyaya|date=12 August 2018|website=International Business Times, India Edition}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nPonnambalam joined the [[All India Anna Dravida Munnetra Kazhagam]] (AIADMK) in February 2011, beginning a career in politics.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tamil.filmibeat.com/news/2-actors-ponnambalam-ceylon-manohar-join-admk-aid0091.html|title=\u0b85\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bae\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0ba8\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bca\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0ba9\u0bae\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bb2\u0bae\u0bcd, \u0baa\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0b95\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcb\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0bae\u0ba9\u0bcb\u0b95\u0bb0\u0bcd|date=2 February 2011|website=https://tamil.filmibeat.com}}</ref> He campaigned for the AIADMK party in the [[Indian general election, 2014 (Tamil Nadu)|Indian general election of 2014]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/aiadmk-to-add-star-power-to-campaign/article5764892.ece|title=AIADMK to add star power to campaign|first=S. Vijay|last=Kumar|date=9 March 2014|via=www.thehindu.com}}</ref> In June 2017, he left the AIADMK and joined the [[Bharatiya Janata Party]] (BJP) in the presence of the Union Minister of State for [[Ministry of Finance (India)|Finance]] and [[Ministry of Shipping (India)|Shipping]], [[Pon Radhakrishnan]]. On joining the party, Ponnambalam stated that no other party seemed \"concerned about the welfare of people\" and hence, he decided to join the BJP.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiaglitz.com/popular-villain-actor-switches-over-to-bjp-from-admk-tamil-news-187636.html|title=Popular villain actor switches over to BJP from ADMK - Tamil News|date=14 June 2017|website=IndiaGlitz.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/nation/politics/150617/tamil-nadu-actor-ponnambalam-joins-bjps-star-bandwagon.html|title=Tamil Nadu: Actor Ponnambalam joins BJP\u2019s star bandwagon|date=15 June 2017|website=Deccan Chronicle}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Actor===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! Year !! Film !! Role !! Language !! Notes\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"| 1988 || ''[[Kaliyugam (1988 film)|Kaliyugam]]''