'' ||  || Telugu ||\n|-\n| ''[[Masti (2007 film)|Masti]]'' || || Kannada ||\n|-\n| ''[[Police Story 2 (2007 film)|Police Story 2]]'' || || Kannada ||\n|-\n|rowspan=\"7\"| 2008 || ''[[Pattaya Kelappu]]'' || Anandakrishnan || Tamil || Also director\n|-\n| ''[[Vaitheeswaran]]'' || || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Aayudham Seivom]]'' || || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Ezhuthiyatharadi]]'' || Pandi || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Theeyavan]]'' || || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Channa (film)|Channa]]'' || || Kannada ||\n|-\n| ''[[Bujjigadu]]'' || || Telugu ||\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"| 2009 || ''[[Thee (2009 film)|Thee]]'' || Saleem || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Madurai Sambavam]]'' || || Tamil || \n|-\n| ''[[Oru Kadhalan Oru Kadhali]]'' || Lingesu || Tamil || \n|-\n|rowspan=\"8\"| 2010 || ''[[Thamizh Padam]]'' || Nattamai || Tamil || \n|-\n| ''[[Aarvam]]'' || || Tamil || \n|-\n| ''[[Androru Naal]]'' || || Tamil || \n|-\n| ''[[Athisaya Manal Matha]]'' || || Tamil || \n|-\n| ''[[Bayam Ariyaan]]'' || || Tamil || \n|-\n| ''[[Innisai Kavalan]]'' || || Tamil || \n|-\n| ''[[Puzhal (film)|Puzhal]]'' || || Tamil || \n|-\n| ''[[Nagaram Marupakkam]]'' || 'Thala Vetti' Thangarasu || Tamil || \n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"| 2011 || ''[[Bhavani IPS]]'' || || Tamil || \n|-\n| ''[[Ponnar Shankar (film)|Ponnar Shankar]]'' || Thalapathi || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Venghai]]'' || Anburaja || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Mudhal Idam]]'' ||  || Tamil ||\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\"| 2012 || ''[[Maasi (film)|Maasi]]'' || Nandha || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Mattuthavani (film)|Mattuthavani]]'' || || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Ullam (2012 film)|Ullam]]'' || || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Arakkonam (film)|Arakkonam]]'' || || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Virudhunagar Sandhippu]]'' || || Tamil ||\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"| 2013 || ''Keeripulla'' ||  || Tamil ||\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| 2014 || ''Madhavanum Malarvizhiyum'' ||  || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''Adhu Vera Idhu Vera'' || Police Inspector || Tamil ||\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| 2016 || ''[[Enakku Innoru Per Irukku]]'' || Cameo appearance || Tamil || \n|-\n| ''[[Parandhu Sella Vaa]]'' || Ponnambalam || Tamil ||\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| 2017 || ''[[12-12-1950]]'' || Police Inspector || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Aadu 2]]'' || Mayilvahanam || Malayalam || \n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2018 || ''Pei Irukka Illaya'' ||  || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''Thulam'' || || Tamil ||\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| 2019 || ''[[Comali]]'' || Gaaja || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''Chennai 2 Bangkok'' || || Tamil || Special appearance\n|-\n|}\n\n===Stuntman===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! Year !! Film !! Language\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\" | 1987 || ''[[Shankar Guru (1987 film)|Shankar Guru]]'' || Tamil\n|-\n| ''[[Per Sollum Pillai]]'' || Tamil \n|-\n| ''Vairakkiyam'' || Tamil\n|-\n|rowspan=\"10\" | 1988 || ''[[Sathya (1988 film)|Sathya]]'' || Tamil\n|-\n| ''[[En Thangai Kalyani]]'' || Tamil\n|-\n| ''[[Puthiya Vaanam]]'' || Tamil\n|-\n| ''[[Soora Samhaaram]]'' || Tamil\n|-\n| ''[[Thaimel Aanai]]'' || Tamil\n|-\n| ''Poovizhi Raja'' || Tamil\n|-\n| ''Pattikaatu Thambi'' || Tamil\n|-\n| ''Dhayam Onnu'' || Tamil\n|-\n| ''[[Katha Nayagan (1988 film)|Katha Nayagan]]'' || Tamil\n|-\n| ''[[Kaliyugam (1988 film)|Kaliyugam]]'' || Tamil\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\" | 1989 || ''[[Apoorva Sagodharargal (1989 film)|Apoorva Sagodharargal]]'' || Tamil\n|-\n| ''[[Padicha Pulla]]'' || Tamil\n|-\n| ''[[Annanukku Jai]]'' || Tamil\n|-\n| ''[[Vettaiyaadu Vilaiyaadu (1989 film)|Vettaiyaadu Vilaiyaadu]]'' || Tamil\n|-\n| ''[[En Thangai (1989 film)|En Thangai]]'' || Tamil\n|-\n| ''Vetri Mel Vetri'' || Tamil\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\"| 1990 || ''[[Avasara Police 100]]'' || Tamil\n|-\n| ''[[Sathriyan]]'' || Tamil\n|-\n| ''[[Urudhi Mozhi]]'' || Tamil\n|-\n| ''[[Raja Kaiya Vacha]]'' || Tamil\n|-\n| ''[[My Dear Marthandan]]'' || Tamil\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"| 1991 || ''[[Captain Prabhakaran]]'' || Tamil\n|-\n| ''[[Maanagara Kaaval]]'' || Tamil\n|-\n| ''[[Moondrezhuthil En Moochirukkum]]'' || Tamil\n|}\n\n=== Television ===\n* ''[[Bigg Boss Tamil 2]]'' (2018)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|0690448}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ponnambalam}}\n[[Category:Indian male film actors]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Tamil cinema]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:Bigg Boss contestants]]\n", "text_old": "{{Cleanup bare URLs|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Ponnambalam\n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1963|11|11}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nettv4u.com/celebrity/tamil/movie-actor/ponnambalam |title=Tamil Movie Actor Ponnambalam - Nettv4u |publisher= |accessdate=1 October 2016}}</ref>\n| birth_place        = \n| residence          = [[Chennai]], [[Tamil Nadu]], India\n| occupation         = Film actor, stunt performer, film director\n| yearsactive        = 1987\u2013present\n| height             = \n| spouse             = \n| children           = \n}}\n\n'''Ponnambalam''' (born 11 November 1963) is an Indian [[film actor]] who has predominantly appeared in [[Tamil cinema|Tamil]] language films. He is best known for playing antagonistic roles in Indian films during the 1990s, notably appearing in films such as ''[[Nattamai]]'' (1994), ''[[Muthu (1995 film)|Muthu]]'' (1995) and ''[[Amarkalam]]'' (1999).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cinesouth.com/cgi-bin/persondb.cgi?name=ponnambalam |title=\u0b9f\u0bcb\u0b9f\u0bcb\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0bb0\u0b83\u0baa\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bcb\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1 \u2014 Tamil Kavithai -- \u0ba4\u0bae\u0bbf\u0bb4\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd - \u0ba8\u0bc2\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc1 \u0b95\u0ba3\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd! |publisher= |accessdate=1 October 2016}}</ref> Later in his career, Ponnambalam also appeared in a few leading roles, while also taking up the mantle of director and producer.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/interview/6126.html |title=Tamil Celebrity Interview - IndiaGlitz.com |publisher= |accessdate=1 October 2016}}</ref> \n\n==Career==\nPonnambalam made his debut in cinema as a stuntman, and often appeared as an extra fighter in films, starring in minor roles in films including ''[[Apoorva Sagodharargal (1989 film)|Apoorva Sagodharargal]]'' (1989) and ''[[Michael Madana Kama Rajan]]'' (1990). As a result of his proficiency as a stuntman, he later received the nickname \"Spare Parts\" Ponnambalam as no part of his body was ever injured or fractured.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/cinema-veeran-aishwarya-dhanush-pays-a-glorious-tribute-to-the-stuntmen-of-tamil-cinema-3743325.html |title=Cinema Veeran : Aishwarya Dhanush pays a glorious tribute to the stuntmen Of Tamil cinema |date=2017-06-25 |work=Firstpost |access-date=2017-07-19 |language=en-US}}</ref> He made a breakthrough as an actor following the success of [[P. Vasu]]'s ''[[Walter Vetrivel]]'' (1993), and subsequently starred in several prominent Tamil films in the 1990s in villainous roles. Notable characters her portrayed including his work in ''[[Nattamai]]'' (1994), ''[[Muthu (1995 film)|Muthu]]'' (1995) and ''[[Amarkalam]]'' (1999). Ponnambalam also played the lead roles in film including the action drama ''Muthal Echarikkai'' (1999) and ''Ammaiyappa'' (2002), where he featured alongside actress Roshini. Reviewing the film, a critic noted \"the movie does little other than prove conclusively that Ponnambalam is not cut out to be a hero\", and that \"though he picks a role that suits his build, emotes surprisingly well and fights aggressively, his looks make it difficult for us to accept him as a conventional leading man\".<ref>https://jfwonline.com/article/bigg-boss-tamil-all-you-need-to-know-about-this-seasons-contestants/</ref>\n\nPonnambalam turned director and producer through the film, ''[[Pattaya Kelappu]]'', starring [[Sriman (actor)|Sriman]] in the lead role. Despite beginning in 2004, the film had a delayed release, while another directorial venture titled ''Thethi 32'' was subsequently dropped.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tKbxcnWqYYM</ref> Ponnambalam began a project titled ''Idiyudan Koodiya Mazhai'' during 2010, starring newcomers in the lead roles. Despite beginning production, the film was shelved and eventually did not have a theatrical release.<ref>http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/may-10-04/ponnambalam-31-05-10.html</ref> His acting commitments thereafter also decreased, with notable appearances in the period including roles as a village chief in ''[[Thamizh Padam]]'' (2010) and characters in ''[[Venghai]]'' (2011) and the historical drama, ''[[Ponnar Shankar (film)|Ponnar Shankar]]'' (2011).\n\nIn 2018, Ponnambalam took part in the second season of the reality show ''[[Bigg Boss Tamil 2|Bigg Boss Tamil]]'' hosted by [[Kamal Haasan]]. His stay in the house was controversial, as he was accused of making [[misogyny|misogynistic]] comments against the female housemates, particularly against [[Yashika Aanand]], [[Aishwarya Dutta]], Mamathi Chari and [[Mumtaj]] and was nominated each week for the eviction from the second week of the show onwards.<ref>[http://www.sify.com/movies/bigg-boss-2-honour-culture-and-slander-news-tamil-shkqtihfbccci.html Bigg Boss 2: Honour, Culture and Slander]</ref> He was evicted during the eighth week of the show during mid-August 2018.<ref>[https://www.ibtimes.co.in/bigg-boss-tamil-eviction-live-sendrayan-escapes-ponnambalam-janani-exit-kamals-show-says-ibt-777619 Bigg Boss Tamil 2 eviction: Ponnambalam is the sixth contestant to be eliminated from Kamal Haasan's show]</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nPonnambalam joined the [[All India Anna Dravida Munnetra Kazhagam]] (AIADMK) in February 2011, beginning a career in politics.<ref>https://tamil.filmibeat.com/news/2-actors-ponnambalam-ceylon-manohar-join-admk-aid0091.html</ref> He campaigned for the AIADMK party in the [[Indian general election, 2014 (Tamil Nadu)|Indian general election of 2014]].<ref>http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/aiadmk-to-add-star-power-to-campaign/article5764892.ece</ref> In June 2017, he left the AIADMK and joined the [[Bharatiya Janata Party]] (BJP) in the presence of the Union Minister of State for [[Ministry of Finance (India)|Finance]] and [[Ministry of Shipping (India)|Shipping]], [[Pon Radhakrishnan]]. On joining the party, Ponnambalam stated that no other party seemed \"concerned about the welfare of people\" and hence, he decided to join the BJP.<ref>https://www.indiaglitz.com/popular-villain-actor-switches-over-to-bjp-from-admk-tamil-news-187636.html</ref><ref>https://www.deccanchronicle.com/nation/politics/150617/tamil-nadu-actor-ponnambalam-joins-bjps-star-bandwagon.html</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Actor===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! Year !! Film !! Role !! Language !! Notes\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"| 1988 || ''[[Kaliyugam (1988 film)|Kaliyugam]]'' || Prisoner || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Moonnam Mura]]'' || Peter || Malayalam || \n|-\n| ''[[Orkkapurathu]]'' || || Malayalam || \n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| 1989 || ''[[Apoorva Sagodharargal (1989 film)|Apoorva Sagodharargal]]'' || || Tamil || \n|-\n| ''[[Vetri Vizha]]'' || || Tamil || \n|-\n| 1990 || ''[[Michael Madana Kama Rajan]]'' || Assassin 1 || Tamil ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" | 1991 || ''[[Vetri Padigal]]'' || || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Pudhu Manithan]]'' || || Tamil ||\n|-\n|[[Maanagara Kaaval]]\n|\n|Tamil\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Moondrezhuthil En Moochirukkum]]'' || Rogue || Tamil ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"9\" | 1992 || ''[[Naangal]]'' ||  || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Gharana Mogudu]]'' || Veeraiyah || Telugu ||\n|-\n| ''[[Thangarasu]]'' || || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Bharathan (1992 film)|Bharathan]]'' ||  Gangadharan's right hand || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Naalaya Seidhi]]'' || || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Kottai Vaasal]]'' || || Tamil ||\n|-\n|[[Senthamizh Paattu]]\n|\n|Tamil\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Ellaichami]]'' || Balaya